description: Return a list of App Runner VPC Ingress Connections in your Amazon Web Services account.

parameters.name: Filter
parameters.description: The VPC Ingress Connections to be listed based on either the Service Arn or Vpc Endpoint Id, or both. ServiceArn (string) --- The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of a service to filter by. VpcEndpointId (string) --- The ID of a VPC Endpoint to filter by.

nested_params.name: ServiceArn
nested_params.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of a service to filter by.

nested_params.name: VpcEndpointId
nested_params.description: The ID of a VPC Endpoint to filter by.

parameters.name: MaxResults
parameters.description: The maximum number of results to include in each response (result page). It's used for a paginated request. If you don't specify MaxResults, the request retrieves all available results in a single response.

parameters.name: NextToken
parameters.description: A token from a previous result page. It's used for a paginated request. The request retrieves the next result page. All other parameter values must be identical to the ones that are specified in the initial request. If you don't specify NextToken, the request retrieves the first result page.

nested_items.name: VpcIngressConnectionSummaryList
nested_items.description: A list of summary information records for VPC Ingress Connections. In a paginated request, the request returns up to MaxResults records for each call.

nested_items.name: VpcIngressConnectionArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the VPC Ingress Connection.

nested_items.name: ServiceArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the service associated with the VPC Ingress Connection.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The token that you can pass in a subsequent request to get the next result page. It's returned in a paginated request.
